FORMER governor of Osun State and first interim national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Chief Bisi Akande, on Thursday evening, gifted the incumbent governor of the state, Adegboyega Oyetola, a horse which he said he should ride to power. Governor Oyetola had, after his strategic engagement tour of Ila Federal Constituency, visited Akande at his residence in Ila where he got the gift. The tour is a statewide consultation to the nine federal constituencies in Osun State which the governor is using to fraternise with the newly elected APC executive at the ward and local government levels and to inform them and party members of his intention to participate in the partyâ€™s forthcoming primary in preparation for the July governorship election. ALSO READ FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE The presentation of the horse to the governor by Chief Akande was seen as symbolising a declaration of support for the person and candidature of Oyetola. While accepting the gift, Governor Oyetola, who was obviously surprised and excited with smiles on his face, profusely thanked Chief Akande